<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1081" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1081">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15951.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Brownsville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Nafarrate, Commander of this district, personally called last
                            night and assured me that he had given strict orders to his men to
                            retire some distance from river front and disposed to assist in every
                            way possible to prevent further trouble.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">E. J. Puig.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>